 human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":5,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1705192,"age":18,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1705195,"age":72,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":3}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Beke was born about 1310. He married Alice of Blore Heath. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1422, in Eresby, Spilsby, Lincolnshire, England, at the age of 113."},"et":{"Abt 1310–1422":"umbes 1310–1422","1317–Female":"1317–Surnud","1336–1408":"1336–1408","1310–1422":"1310–1422","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","20 September 1408":"20. september 1408","1422":"1422","Abt 1310":"umbes 1310","1310":"1310","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","15 September 1336":"15. september 1336","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Blore Ray, Staffordshire, England":"Blore Ray, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Eresby, Spilsby, Lincolnshire, England":"Eresby, Spilsby, Lincolnshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},